<h2 id="preface-">Preface <a id="first"></a></h2>
<p>I created a script file in this post: <a href="https://myoiwritescode.github.io/linux/2019/06/30/en-linux-disable-keyboard.html">[Ubuntu] Disable Laptop Keyboard</a>, that switches on/off the internal keyboard.
I was trying to move the file <code class="highlighter-rouge">kbd-onoff.bat</code> to <code class="highlighter-rouge">/bin</code> and I accidentally did this:</p>
<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>$ sudo mv kbd-onoff.bat /bin/bash
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>And the chaos began.</p>

<p><br /></p>
<h2 id="troubleshoot-">Troubleshoot <a id="issue"></a></h2>

<p>I noticed the error right away because my terminal stopped working.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/images/linux/restore-bash/error1.png" alt="Error image 1" /></p>

<p>My first attempt was to reinstall bash. Since I cannot use my terminal,
  I went to <code class="highlighter-rouge">Preference -&gt; Command</code> and selected <code class="highlighter-rouge">Run a custom command insteal of my shell</code>.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/images/linux/restore-bash/custom-command.png" alt="Custom command image 1" /></p>

<p>Unfortunately above process did not work.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/images/linux/restore-bash/error2.png" alt="Error image 2" /></p>

<p><br /></p>
<h2 id="solution-">Solution <a id="solution"></a></h2>
<p>I learned from googling that in most of the system <code class="highlighter-rouge">/bin/bash</code> is actually just a symlink to 
<code class="highlighter-rouge">/bin/sh</code>. So what if I create new symlink <code class="highlighter-rouge">/bin/bash</code> to <code class="highlighter-rouge">/bin/sh</code> and then reinstall bash?</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>rm -rf /bin/bash
ln -s /bin/sh /bin/bash
apt-get install --reinstall bash
</code></pre></div></div>

<p><img src="/assets/images/linux/restore-bash/solution.png" alt="Solution image" /></p>

<p>Voila! My bash is back.</p>

<p><br /></p>
